# Floyd Warshall
Distance matrix for network nodes A, B, C, D, E:

       A     B     C     D     E
A  [   0,    3,  INF,    7,  INF ]
B  [   8,    0,    2,  INF,  INF ]
C  [   5,  INF,    0,    1,  INF ]
D  [   2,  INF,  INF,    0,    3 ]
E  [ INF,  INF,    4,  INF,    0 ]

Apply Floyd-Warshall algorithm to find shortest distances between ALL pairs of nodes.
Show the result as a heatmap.

# Kruskal - Minimum Spanning Tree
We need to connect 6 office buildings with network cables.
The cost (meters of cable) between each pair:

Edges (building1, building2, cable_length):
(HQ,    Finance,   10)
(HQ,    IT,         6)
(HQ,    HR,         5)
(Finance, IT,       15)
(Finance, HR,       8)
(Finance, Sales,    12)
(IT,    HR,          4)
(IT,    Sales,       9)
(HR,    Sales,      11)
(Sales, Warehouse,   7)
(IT,    Warehouse,  13)

Find the Minimum Spanning Tree to connect all buildings with minimum cable.
Use Kruskal's algorithm.

